A clone of neurons in the adult female that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral abdominal ganglion. It is composed of ascending neurons that innervate the three leg pairs and the subesophageal zone, terminating in the superior lateral protocerebrum. It is a sexually dimorphic clone: neuron arborization in the subesophageal zone is ventral to male vAB3 clones.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron with its cell body in the ventral abdominal neuromere and arbors in the vicinity of the fore-, mid- and hindleg afferents (Yu et al., 2010). It has an ascending axonal projection that innervates the subesophageal zone (SEZ) and lateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). Its SEZ arbors are located more dorsally than those of the male equivalent (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral abdominal ganglion. It is composed of ascending neurons that innervate the three leg pairs and the subesophageal zone, terminating in the superior lateral protocerebrum. It is a sexually dimorphic clone: neuron arborization in the subesophageal zone is dorsal to female vAB3 clones.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron with its cell body in the ventral abdominal neuromere and arbors in the vicinity of the fore-, mid- and hindleg afferents (Yu et al., 2010). It has an ascending axonal projection that innervates the subesophageal zone (SEZ) and lateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). Its SEZ arbors are located more ventrally than those of the female equivalent (Yu et al., 2010).

Male-specific fruitless neuron with its soma in the medial posterior brain (von Phillipsborn et al., 2011). It extends neurites bilaterally innervating the periesophageal region and the lateral protocerebrum; one long process descends to the ventral nerve cord, where it extensively innervates the wing neuropil (von Phillipsborn et al., 2011). There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it is cholinergic (Lillvis et al., 2024). It is involved in pulse and sine song generation (von Phillipsborn et al., 2011; O'Sullivan et al., 2018; Lillvis et al., 2024).

Male-specific fruitless neuron with its soma in the anterior prothoracic neuromere (von Philipsborn et al., 2011). It innervates the wing neuropil bilaterally (von Philipsborn et al., 2011). It plays a role in male pulse song (von Philipsborn et al., 2011; Lillvis et al., 2024). There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it also expresses doublesex (von Philipsborn et al., 2011; Lillvis et al., 2024). It is cholinergic (Lillvis et al., 2024).

definition.value: Might be a subtype of TN2 dsx neuron (von Philipsborn et al., 2011).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral anterior region of the prothoracic ganglion close to the midline. Its neurons extend neurites into the brain to innervate the medial ring in the protocerebrum. It projects posteriorly forming arborizations in a distinct 'A' shape extending to the anterior of the mesothoracic segment. This clone is not found in females.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located at the anterior of the prothoracic neuromere, close to the midline (Yu et al., 2010). It enters the anterior prothoracic neuromere and projects posteriorly forming arborizations in an 'A' shape extending into the mesothoracic neuromere bilaterally (Yu et al., 2010; Lillvis et al., 2024). A branch projects to the brain to form axonal arbors in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). There are approximately 16 of these cells per organism and they are cholinergic (Lillvis et al., 2024).

A clone of neurons in the male adult ventral nerve cord that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located laterally near the border of the prothoracic and mesothoracic ganglia. Its neurons extend neurites medially and posteriorly within the wing neuropil. This clone is dimorphic, with differences in arborization in the mesothoracic triangle between males and females.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that is derived from hemilineage 12A and has a ventrolateral cell body, between the first and second thoracic neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010; Shirangi et al., 2016). It has bilateral arborization in the dorsal mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010; Shirangi et al., 2016). It plays a role in male courtship song (Shirangi et al., 2016).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) map this to Cachero et al. (2010) vPR-k, which is not dimorphic and has additional arborization in the prothoracic neuromere.

value.value: Small cell found in the lower part of the tubule and in the ureter. It contains a reduced cytoplasm, a compact nucleus and thin processes and it lies close to the tubular walls. They are distinct from the stellate cells.

definition.value: These cells may be neurosecretory (Sozen et al., 1997). In the adult they are stem cells (Singh et al., 2007; Wang and Spradling, 2020). Tiny cells are also found in the posterior midgut (Sozen et al., 1997).

value.value: Stem cell of the adult Malpighian tubule (Singh et al., 2007). These are small cells occupying a basal position and are only found in the lower tubule and ureter (stem cell zone) (Singh et al., 2007; Wang and Spradling, 2020). They are usually quiescent, but can generate replacement principal cells in response to injury (Wang and Spradling, 2020). Within the stem cell zone, they are more numerous than type I (principal) cells (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

definition.value: Can be identified by expression of escargot (Singh et al., 2007; Wang and Spradling, 2020).

value.value: Tiny cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubules.
Tiny cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubules.
Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies dorsoposterior to glomerulus VP3, ventral to DP1.

definition.value: Discernible with Golgi impregnation, but not with nc82/bruchtpilot immunolabelling, according to Tanaka et al. (2012) this glomerulus corresponds to part of the innervation region of IR40a ORNs, identified as the 'arm' by Silbering et al. (2011). Although VP1 and VP4 glomeruli are innervated by IR40a neurons, these correspond to different subsets and are therefore considered different glomeruli (Tanaka et al., 2012).
